There is a missmatch with the neutralMinionsKilled key of the ParticipantFrameData and the name under which it has been renamed, namely neutralMinionsKilled and NeutralMinionsKilled:

in cassiopeia/core/match.py:

line 530-532
```python
@property
    def neutral_minions_killed(self) -> int:
        return self._data[ParticipantFrameData].neutralMinionsKilled
```

line 90-91
```python
class ParticipantFrameData(CoreData):
    _renamed = {"totalGold": "goldEarned", "minionsKilled": "creepScore", "xp": "experience", "jungleMinionsKilled": "NeutralMinionsKilled"}
```

Currently, `DjangoObjectType` uses `help_text` from Django model fields to populate the description of fields in the schema. As I don't use help texts at the model level in my project, all the autogenerated fields in my schema have empty descriptions, unless I override them with Graphene fields. Wouldn't it be more convenient to override only the descriptions from the metaclass?

Example:

```
class Product(DjangoObjectType):
    class Meta:
        descriptions = {
            "name": "The product's name",
            "description": "The product's description"}
        model = models.Product
```

This is similar to how `ModelForm` API allows overriding help texts, labels or widgets. My goal is to have all the fields in API documented and I think this would help me a lot. What do you think?

Add prefix field option in filter context.

https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/query-dsl-prefix-query.html

For reply as this demand with arlas :

```curl -XPOST 'localhost:9200/level0_enriched/_search?size=0&pretty' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d'
{
    "aggs": {
        "relevant_terms": {
            "filter": {
                "prefix": {
                    "relevant_terms": "P"
                }
            },
            "aggs": {
                "relevant_terms": {
                    "terms": {
                        "field": "relevant_terms",
                        "include": "P.*"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}'```
